                    "_comment": "Inertial impaction term of the collection efficiency (Eq. 20.53, third line; slinn_collection_efficiency, src line 351): E_imp = E_imp_unscaled*density_scaling",
                    "lhs": "E_imp",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "*",
                        "args": [
                            "E_imp_unscaled",
                            "density_scaling"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Sum of the three collection-efficiency mechanisms before clamping (slinn_collection_efficiency, src line 353): E_total = E_diff + E_int + E_imp",
                    "lhs": "E_total",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "+",
                        "args": [
                            "E_diff",
                            "E_int",
                            "E_imp"
                        ]
                    }
                },
                {
                    "_comment": "Collection efficiency clamped to a maximum of 1 (Eq. 20.53; slinn_collection_efficiency, src line 355): E = min(1, E_total). Upstream writes ifelse(E_total > 1, 1, E_total); min(1, E_total) is the identical upper clamp and the spec §4.2-preferred AST encoding of a clamp/limiter.",
                    "lhs": "E",
                    "rhs": {
                        "op": "min",
                        "args": [
                            1,
                            "E_total"
                        ]
                    }
                }
            ],
            "tests": [
                {
                    "id": "default_parameters",
                    "description": "Component defaults (D_p = 1 mm raindrop, U_t = 4 m/s, d_p = 1 µm accumulation-mode aerosol, ρ_p = 1000 kg/m^3, T = 298 K). These inputs coincide with the upstream helper-function test inputs, so τ, u_t_particle, and D_diff are pinned against the upstream reference values (particle_relaxation_time ≈ 3.23e-6 s, particle_terminal_velocity ≈ 3.17e-5 m/s, particle_diffusivity ≈ 2.54e-11 m^2/s). The Stokes number St ≈ 0.026 falls below the critical S* ≈ 0.27, so the impaction term is off and E is the sum of the small Brownian and interception terms. The system is algebraic, so E is re-asserted at t = 1 to confirm time-invariance.",
                    "parameter_overrides": {
                        "D_p": 0.001,
                        "U_t": 4.0,
                        "d_p": 1e-06,
                        "ρ_p": 1000.0,
                        "T": 298.0
                    },
                    "time_span": {
                        "start": 0.0,
                        "end": 1.0
                    },
